The paper deals with scheduling and packet collisions in wireless networks, which are topics related to information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The proposed solution involves coding techniques, which are also relevant to distributed computing (cs.DC) and signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the paper presents theoretical results on the complexity of the proposed method, which could be of interest to machine learning researchers (cs.LG).
